      "writtenOn": "2017-05-16T18:02:45Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "\u003e glibc 2.19.\n\u003e The kernel and linux/elf.h use NT_PRFPREG.\n\u003e elf.h and other glibc sources define it as NT_FPREGSET.\n\u003e \n\u003e elf.h on Android at API 21 includes linux/elf.h so it gets NT_PRFPREG\n\nI see.\n\nAt that point, it would actually be an argument in favor of using \u003clinux/elf.h\u003e in preference to or in addition to \u003celf.h\u003e, if possible. But if that’s not possible, what you have now is good.",
