    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "9e9fb7e3_e4373cdf",
        "filename": "compat/linux/sys/ptrace.h",
        "patchSetId": 20
      },
      "lineNbr": 20,
      "author": {
        "id": 1172779
      },
      "writtenOn": "2017-05-16T17:11:03Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "On my workstation, Linux 4.4.0-75, glibc 2.19\n\nglibc declares its ptrace wrapper as:\nextern long int ptrace (enum __ptrace_request __request, ...) __THROW;\nand does not provide an enum value for PTRACE_ARCH_PRCTL.\n\nasm/ptrace-abi.h provides\n#define PTRACE_ARCH_PRCTL 30\nwhich should work for the raw system call, but not the glibc wrapper.\n\nI added a check for __GLIBC__.\nI think the alternative is to use the raw system call?",
      "parentUuid": "64ebc59e_2d131877",
      "revId": "86ccb582c47070c865ada7ba998609af66e43cae",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
