      "writtenOn": "2017-05-15T18:40:15Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Probably I’d simplify by having something like:\n\n  #if defined(ARCH_CPU_ARMEL)\n  using NativeThreadContext \u003d user_regs;\n  #elif defined(ARCH_CPU_X86_FAMILY) || defined(ARCH_CPU_ARM64)\n  using NativeThreadContext \u003d user_regs_struct;\n  #else\n  #error Port.\n  #endif\n\n(That’s basically what PrStatusType, now being removed, was.)\n\nThen, for your static_asserts, everything boils down to:\n\n  #if defined(ARCH_CPU_32_BITS)\n  static_assert(sizeof(t32) \u003d\u003d sizeof(NativeThreadContext));\n  #else\n  static_assert(sizeof(t64) \u003d\u003d sizeof(NativeThreadContext));\n  #endif",
      "revId": "86ccb582c47070c865ada7ba998609af66e43cae",
